  Before writing a single word, decide EXACTLY which images this
  article needs. Use the IMAGE BRIEF TEMPLATE below. This prevents
  writing an article and then discovering you have no real screenshots.

  IMAGE BRIEF TEMPLATE (fill this out at pre-write stage):
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Article slug: ___________                               │
  │ Article type: tutorial / comparison / listicle / other  │
  │ Category accent color: ___________                      │
  │                                                         │
  │ Image 1 (first 500 words): ___________                  │
  │ Image 2: ___________                                    │
  │ Image 3: ___________                                    │
  │ Image 4+: ___________                                   │
  │                                                         │
  │ OG stat: val=___ label=___                              │
  │ Real screenshots needed (list): ___________             │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STEP 1 — FEATURED IMAGE (OG / Social Share)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Size: 1200x630px PNG, under 150KB, dark background
  Generate: node /var/www/blixamo/tools/generate-og-images.js --slug <slug>

  OG STAT (top-right big number) — pick ONE per article type:
  Comparison (A vs B)   → winner advantage   "3x cheaper", "1 failed"
  Tutorial/how-to       → time to complete   "30m", "4h to build"
  Listicle              → count or saving    "Free", "7 tested", "₹0"
  Cost/pricing          → saving or price    "60% cheaper", "₹465/mo"
  Tool review           → key metric         "306ms", "2s startup"
  Automation/workflow   → outcome            "3h/week saved", "90d uptime"
  BAD: "10m read time", "12m read time" — zero information value

  ADD TO OVERRIDES before generating:
  File: /var/www/blixamo/tools/generate-og-images.js → const OVERRIDES = {
  Add:  'your-slug': { val: 'X', label: 'your label' },

  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STEP 2 — IN-ARTICLE IMAGE BRIEF BY ARTICLE TYPE
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  DECISION TREE — run this before every article:

  Does this article have real terminal commands / real results?
    YES → SCREENSHOT IT (highest E-E-A-T signal, cannot be faked)
  Does this article compare costs or tools?
    YES → MAKE A BAR CHART (Ideogram 3.0 — renders ₹ accurately)
  Does this article explain a multi-step system?
    YES → MAKE A FLOW DIAGRAM (Midjourney v7 or Canva)
  Does this article review/introduce a tool?
    YES → SHOW THE TOOL UI (real screenshot or AI mockup)
  Does this article have a before/after transformation?
    YES → MAKE A PROOF CARD (Ideogram 3.0)

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TUTORIAL / HOW-TO  (min 5 images)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  [ ] Image 1 — Architecture/flow diagram (first 500 words)
      Shows the full system BEFORE reader starts following steps
      Tool: Midjourney v7 or Canva
      Prompt base: "Clean technical flow diagram, dark #0a0a0f bg,
      teal accent lines, white node text, showing [YOUR FLOW],
      flat minimal design, 1200x630 --ar 16:9 --v 7"

  [ ] Image 2 — First terminal screenshot (step 1-2 region)
      Real screenshot of your actual terminal output
      Annotate with red arrow/box in Canva if needed
      Must show: the command AND its successful output

  [ ] Image 3 — Mid-point proof screenshot (step 3-4 region)
      Something visible changed — dashboard, file created, service running
      Real screenshot preferred over AI mockup

  [ ] Image 4 — Final result screenshot
      The working end state. Live site, running service, success response.
      This is the most important image — reader is scanning for "does it work?"

  [ ] Image 5 — Error screenshot (Troubleshooting section)
      Show the actual error message + the fix side by side
      Makes the troubleshooting section credible

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  COMPARISON / VS  (min 6 images)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ⭐ STANDALONE TWEET IMAGE REQUIRED for every comparison article.
  Must make sense with zero context — no article title, no caption.
  Use as both Image 1 (in-article) AND tweet attachment on publish.
  Tool: Ideogram 3.0. Format: verdict card or cost bar chart.

  [ ] Image 1 — Cost/spec bar chart (first 500 words, after TL;DR)
      Horizontal bars, dark bg, teal vs red/amber colors
      Tool: Ideogram 3.0 (use for any image with ₹ numbers)
      Prompt: "Minimalist horizontal bar chart, dark #0d0d1a bg,
      white labels, teal and red bars, title '[A] vs [B] Cost in INR',
      flat design, no gradients, 1200x630px"

  [ ] Image 2 — Tool A UI screenshot (Tool A section)
  [ ] Image 3 — Tool B UI screenshot (Tool B section)
      Real screenshots strongly preferred. AI mockup only if tool
      is unavailable. Must show the RELEVANT feature, not just homepage.

  [ ] Image 4 — Side-by-side comparison screenshot or table visual
      Show the same action in both tools
      Tool: Canva side-by-side template

  [ ] Image 5 — Winner proof screenshot
      Show the specific moment where winner clearly beats loser
      e.g. load test results, deploy time, error log

  [ ] Image 6 — Before/after or verdict card
      Tool: Ideogram 3.0
      Prompt: "Before/after card, dark #0d0d1a bg, left 'BEFORE [bad]'
      in red, right 'AFTER [good]' in teal, center →, flat design, 1200x630"

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  LISTICLE  (min 4 images)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ⭐ STANDALONE TWEET IMAGE REQUIRED for every listicle.
  A summary grid or ranked chart that works as a tweet with no article context.
  Tool: Ideogram 3.0 or Canva. Use as Image 1 + tweet attachment.

  [ ] Image 1 — Hero grid or summary chart (first 500 words)
      Shows all items at once — reader gets full picture immediately
      Tool: Canva grid template or Ideogram 3.0

  [ ] Image 2-4 — UI screenshot for top 3 items
      One screenshot per top-ranked item showing key feature
      Real screenshots preferred

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  COST / PAYMENT / INDIA-SPECIFIC  (min 3 images)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  [ ] Image 1 — Proof card showing exact cost (first 500 words)
      Tool: Ideogram 3.0 (critical — ₹ numbers must render correctly)
      Prompt: "Minimal proof card, dark #0d0d1a, large '₹X/month'
      teal text center, subtitle 'Tested March 2026', flat design"

  [ ] Image 2 — Success screenshot (payment confirmed / card approved)
      Real screenshot of successful transaction or approval

  [ ] Image 3 — Error screenshot (what fails and why)
      Real screenshot of the error + caption explaining the fix

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  AI / AUTOMATION  (min 4 images)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  [ ] Image 1 — Flow diagram (first 500 words)
      Full pipeline: input → processing → output
      Tool: Midjourney v7
      Prompt: "Technical automation flow diagram, dark #0a0a0f,
      purple #7c3aed accent, white node labels, arrows between steps,
      showing [YOUR PIPELINE], minimal flat, 1200x630 --ar 16:9 --v 7"

  [ ] Image 2 — Code/API response terminal screenshot
      Real API call output in your actual terminal

  [ ] Image 3 — Dashboard or workflow UI screenshot
      n8n canvas, Telegram bot response, WhatsApp message — real

  [ ] Image 4 — Cost/result proof card
      Tool: Ideogram 3.0
      Show the ₹ cost per call or monthly saving

  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STEP 3 — IMAGE CREATION TOOLS (ranked by use case)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Real terminal screenshots    → Flameshot (Linux) / Snipping Tool (Windows)
                                 ALWAYS preferred — E-E-A-T cannot be faked
  Bar charts / cost tables     → Ideogram 3.0 (free 10/day) — renders ₹ at 95%
  Architecture / flow diagrams → Midjourney v7 — best composition quality
  Before/after proof cards     → Ideogram 3.0 — text accuracy critical
  UI mockups (tool UIs)        → Canva free tier OR auto-generator on VPS
  Annotations (arrows, boxes)  → Canva — add red arrow over any screenshot

  MASTER PROMPT BASE (paste into any tool, fill [BRACKETS]):
  "[DESCRIPTION], dark background #0d0d1a, accent color [COLOR],
  white primary text, gray secondary text #a1a1aa, flat design,
  no gradients, no stock photos, professional developer blog aesthetic,
  1200x630px --ar 16:9"

  CATEGORY ACCENT COLORS:
  AI articles   → purple #7c3aed
  Tools         → amber  #d97706
  Tutorials     → cyan   #0891b2
  Tech/VPS      → green  #059669
  Indie-dev     → red    #e11d48

  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  STEP 4 — FILE RULES
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Path:     /public/images/posts/[slug]/01-name.png
  Naming:   01-first-image.png, 02-second-image.png (numbered)
  Max size: 200KB (compress: pngquant --quality=65-85)
  Never fixed px width in MDX — let CSS handle responsive

  MDX syntax:
  ![Descriptive alt text with keyword](/images/posts/[slug]/01-name.png)
  *Caption: what this shows and why it matters*

  ALT TEXT:
  GOOD: "n8n workflow showing Claude API → MDX file → Hetzner deploy"
  BAD:  "screenshot", "", "image1", "figure 1"

  PLACEMENT:
  — Image 1: after TL;DR box, BEFORE first H2 — always, no exceptions
    (13ms rule: reader scans before reading — Image 1 is the pitch)
  — Image 1 for tutorials: real terminal/result screenshot preferred over illustration
  — Image 1 for comparisons/listicles: the standalone tweet-ready card
  — 1 image per major H2 section minimum
  — Never 2 consecutive H2s without an image
  — Always AFTER the paragraph it illustrates
  — Never between a heading and its first paragraph

  ⚠️  CODE-ONLY content does NOT count as images.
  ASCII diagrams, text trees, code blocks = zero image credit.
  Every article needs at least 1 real screenshot (terminal/browser/dashboard).

RULE 11 — TL;DR BOXRULE 11 — TL;DR BOX
  Use <Callout type="info" title="TL;DR">
  - tick [Best option] — [outcome in 8 words]
  - warn [Middle option] — [caveat in 8 words]
  - cross [Worst option] — [why it fails in 8 words]
  - bulb [Key insight]

RULE 12 — COMPARISON TABLES (two required for vs posts)
  QUICK TABLE after TL;DR: 3 cols max, 4-6 rows
  FULL TABLE before FAQ: all attributes, 6-10+ rows
  Markdown syntax only. Never HTML. Max 3 columns (Rule 31).

RULE 13 — DECISION FRAMEWORK
  ## Which One Should You Use?
  **Choose [A] if:** [3 bullets]
  **Choose [B] if:** [3 bullets]

RULE 14 — WHAT NEXT CTA
  ## What Next?
  [1-2 sentences] + [internal link] + subscribe line + Fiverr CTA

RULE 15 — ANTI-FILLER BANNED WORDS
  certainly, delve, leverage, comprehensive, it's worth noting,
  in today's fast-paced world, seamless, game-changer, cutting-edge,
  utilize, furthermore, moreover, in conclusion, to summarize,
  developers often, this will help you, everything you need to know

RULE 16 — READABILITY
  Max 3 sentences/paragraph. Language-tagged code blocks.
  Bold: first use of key term OR critical warning ONLY.
  Always digits (3 not three).

RULE 17 — SEARCH INTENT (run BEFORE writing)
  1. Google exact keyword
  2. Top 3: format + length + gaps
  3. PAA -> FAQ H3s
  4. Related Searches -> secondary keywords
  5. Format must match SERP

RULE 18 — AFFILIATE
  Hetzner: 20 EUR credit (every Hetzner article) — 2-3 natural spots
  AdSense: ca-pub-9266447528918260
  Fiverr: fiverr.com/s/m5Lzq0x (What Next CTA)
  Disclosure: "Some links are affiliate links."

RULE 19 — SEMANTIC ENRICHMENT
  Hetzner: VPS, Nginx, PM2, CPX22, Helsinki, Falkenstein, Linux
  India payment: RBI, 3DS, forex, UPI, HDFC, SBI, virtual card
  n8n: workflow automation, webhook, node, trigger, Docker

RULE 20 — BLIXAMO VOICE
  Confident, direct. India-first. Opinionated.
  "Niyo wins. Full stop." not "Niyo is one option you might consider."
  [ ] Sounds like Ankit? [ ] 2+ real numbers? [ ] Zero AI farm sentences?

RULE 21 — PRICING FORMAT
  "5.19 EUR/month (Rs 465)" — EUR first, INR in brackets
  Rate: ~Rs 90/EUR (verify before publishing)

RULE 22 — CODE BLOCKS
  Language tag + filename="" for real files + comment above + real tested commands
  Max 30 lines per block. Max 60 chars per line (Rule 31).
  After EVERY command block -> add expected output in <Callout type="tip">

RULE 23 — TOPICAL CLUSTERS
  hetzner/india hub:    multiple-projects-single-vps
  nextjs/tutorials hub: nextjs-mdx-blog-2026
  deployment hub:       deploy-nextjs-coolify-hetzner
  tools/automation hub: coolify-vs-caprover-2026
  indie-dev/india hub:  indian-debit-cards-dev-tools
  ai/automation hub:    whatsapp-ai-assistant-n8n-claude-api

RULE 24 — SCHEMA
  howto -> HowTo panel | comparison -> table snippets | review -> stars
  faq -> PAA accordion | article -> author byline

RULE 25 — USER SATISFACTION
  Answer in first 200 words. TL;DR + tables + code = skimmable.
  Troubleshooting prevents bounces. FAQ keeps them on page.

RULE 26 — SELF-CONTAINED UNITS (SCU)
  60-180 words. Answers one question completely, standalone.
  Opens every H2 before expanding.
  Test: copy first paragraph -> paste alone -> fully answers H2?

RULE 27 — DATA HOOKS
  1+ stat per 150-200 words. Real numbers only. Never invented.

RULE 28 — CADENCE
  1 article every 3 days. Never dump. After 10 -> 2x/week.

RULE 29 — EXTRACTION TEST (pass all 3)
  1. First 200w -> ChatGPT "answer: [keyword]" -> must answer
  2. FAQ answer standalone -> must make sense alone
  3. H2 first paragraph -> must completely answer H2 question

RULE 30 — PRE-PUBLISH CHECKLIST (zero skips)
  FRONTMATTER:
  [ ] 17 fields, no placeholders
  [ ] Title: keyword first 5 words
  [ ] Description: 150-160 chars
  [ ] Schema: correct type

  CONTENT:
  [ ] Hook: first-person, real result, 30 words max
  [ ] First 200w: passes extraction test
  [ ] TL;DR Callout type="info" present
  [ ] Prerequisites block present (tutorials only)
  [ ] SCU opens every H2
  [ ] Every H2 ends with transition sentence
  [ ] Every major step has "why this matters" explanation
  [ ] Every command has expected output Callout after it
  [ ] 1+ data hook per 150-200 words
  [ ] 2+ Callout boxes total
  [ ] Troubleshooting H2 present
  [ ] FAQ: 6-8 H3 questions (grep **bold** -> EMPTY)
  [ ] What Next CTA present
  [ ] Freshness signal in first 200w

  IMAGES:
  [ ] Image brief was completed at pre-write stage (Rule 33)
  [ ] In-article image count meets minimum for article type (Rule 10)
  [ ] Image 1 lands within first 500 words
  [ ] Every H2 section has at least 1 image
  [ ] No 2 consecutive H2s without an image
  [ ] At least 1 REAL screenshot present (terminal/browser/dashboard)
  [ ] Every image: descriptive alt text with keyword
  [ ] Every image: italic caption directly below it
  [ ] Images numbered: 01-name.png, 02-name.png in /public/images/posts/[slug]/
  [ ] No image over 200KB (pngquant --quality=65-85 if needed)
  [ ] Featured image PNG 1200x630 <150KB
  [ ] OG stat added to generate-og-images.js OVERRIDES (not "Xm read time")
  [ ] node generate-og-images.js --slug <slug> run after adding override

  SEO:
  [ ] Keyword density 1-2%
  [ ] 3-5 internal links, 1 in first 500w
  [ ] 4+ E-E-A-T signals
  [ ] 6-10 H2s
  [ ] LSI terms throughout

  TECHNICAL:
  [ ] Word count in range MIN->MAX for article type (Rule 3)
  [ ] No code line over 60 chars (Rule 31)
  [ ] No table over 3 columns (Rule 31)
  [ ] Anti-filler pass done
  [ ] Code blocks language-tagged
  [ ] Prices EUR+INR
  [ ] wc -w article.mdx run -> report count
  [ ] At least 1 real screenshot present (terminal, browser, or dashboard)
  [ ] Step progress H2s present (mandatory if 4+ steps or 1,500w+)

  BAYESIAN SCORE (all 7+, target 8+):
  [ ] Search intent match [ /10]
  [ ] Hook strength [ /10]
  [ ] AI citation potential [ /10]
  [ ] E-E-A-T density [ /10]
  [ ] User satisfaction [ /10]

RULE 31 — MOBILE CONTENT RULES (NEW v7)
  Code blocks:
  - Max 60 chars per line — break with \ continuation
  - One flag per line for long commands
  - GOOD: docker run \ --name myapp \ -p 3000:3000 \ myimage
  - BAD: docker run --name myapp -p 3000:3000 -e NODE_ENV=prod myimage

  Tables: Max 3 columns. Max 30 chars per cell.
  Paragraphs: Max 3 sentences.
  Lists: Max 8 items per list. Each bullet max 15 words.

RULE 32 — READER ENGAGEMENT (NEW v7)
  Prerequisites block (mandatory for tutorials):
  - <Callout type="info" title="Before you start">
  - Include: [tool] [version], time estimate, "Tested on:" line

  Transition sentences (mandatory):
  - Every H2 MUST end with 1 sentence leading to the next
  - GOOD: "Server is ready — now let's install Coolify."

  "Why this matters" (mandatory after every major step):
  - GOOD: "We add swap because Next.js builds spike to 1.5GB RAM and OOM-kill without it."

  Expected output (mandatory after every command):
  - <Callout type="tip" title="Expected output"> after every command block
  - This prevents 80% of "it's not working" confusion

  Step progress for tutorials (MANDATORY if article has 4+ numbered steps OR is over 1,500 words):
  - H2 format: "## Step 3 of 6 — Configure Nginx"
  - Count total steps first, then number every H2 consistently
  - Never skip numbers or use vague headings like "Next Steps" mid-tutorial
  - Readers must always know where they are and how far they have left

RULE 33 — PRE-WRITE CHECKLIST (v8 — run BEFORE first word)
  [ ] Google exact keyword -> note top 3 format + length + schema
  [ ] Check AI Overview -> note what it cites
  [ ] Scrape PAA questions -> these become FAQ H3s verbatim
  [ ] Check Related Searches -> add to secondaryKeywords
  [ ] Confirm Ankit has real personal experience -> if NO, stop
  [ ] Check Rule 8 live index -> pick 3-5 internal link targets
  [ ] Confirm article type -> apply correct word count from Rule 3
  [ ] Set correct schema type in frontmatter (Rule 24)
  [ ] Identify Hetzner referral placement (2-3 natural spots)

  IMAGE BRIEF (fill out before writing — Rule 10 Step 0):
  [ ] Determine article type → look up image count minimum in Rule 10
  [ ] Run Rule 10 DECISION TREE → identify which image TYPES needed
  [ ] List every real screenshot needed → plan when to take them
  [ ] Decide OG stat (val + label) → add to generate-og-images.js OVERRIDES
  [ ] Pick category accent color → #7c3aed / #d97706 / #0891b2 / #059669 / #e11d48
  [ ] Write Ideogram/Midjourney prompts for non-screenshot images
  [ ] Confirm Image 1 will land within first 500 words
  RULE: Do not start writing until image brief is complete.
        An article planned without images will always fail Rule 10.

RULE 34 — MDX COMPONENTS REFERENCE (NEW v7)
  CALLOUT COMPONENT:
  <Callout type="tip" title="Title">Max 3 sentences inside.</Callout>
  <Callout type="info" ...>   -> blue  -> TL;DR, prerequisites, context
  <Callout type="warning" ...> -> amber -> gotchas, things that break
  <Callout type="danger" ...>  -> red   -> data loss, security, irreversible
  Min 2 Callouts per article. TL;DR MUST use type="info".

  CODE BLOCKS:
  ```bash filename="example.sh"
  # Comment explaining what this does
  your-command --here
  ```
  Always: language tag + filename for real files + comment above
  Max 30 lines. Max 60 chars/line. Expected output Callout after every block.

  IMAGES MDX SYNTAX:
  ![Descriptive alt text with keyword](/images/[slug]/filename.png)
  *Caption: what this shows and why it matters*
  Files: /public/images/[slug]/ numbered: 01-name.png, 02-name.png

  ARTICLE CONTENT SEQUENCE:
  1. HOOK (30 words max, first-person, real number)
  2. AGITATE (2-3 sentences)
  3. PROMISE (what they get)
  4. PROOF (your real result)
  5. TL;DR <Callout type="info">
  6. PREREQUISITES <Callout type="info" title="Before you start">
  7. BODY H2s (SCU + transitions + why + expected output + images)
  8. TROUBLESHOOT H2
  9. FAQ H2 (6-8 x ### H3, 60-180w each)
  10. WHAT NEXT H2

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 WORD COUNT ENFORCEMENT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Run: wc -w article.mdx (subtract ~50 for frontmatter)
  Hit TARGET from Rule 3, not just minimum.
  If below target -> expand: Troubleshooting -> FAQ -> why -> expected output
  NEVER pad with filler. Report final word count in article summary.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 POST-PUBLISH RITUAL
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  1. node /var/www/gsc-tool/gsc.js index <full-url>
  2. node /var/www/gsc-tool/gsc.js submit
  3. Tweet: hook + insight + URL + #IndieHacker #Hetzner #India
  4. Update Rule 8 live article index
  5. Update Rule 23 cluster map
  6. Update cluster hub -> add backlink -> redeploy
  7. Google Rich Results Test -> verify schema
  8. 30 days: extraction test + GSC impressions check

